Package net.dean.jraw.pagination

Contains classes used to paginate through various models such as submissions on the front page

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllSubredditsPaginator
    This paginator will iterate through the newest and most popular subreddits
    Contribution
    This class functions as a "hacky" way to have more than one return type for UserContributionPaginator, which will return both Submissions and Comments.
    GenericPaginator<T extends Thing,U extends java.lang.Enum<U>>
    This class provides a template for Paginators that use only a "where" attribute, such as /user/username/{where}.
    MySubredditsPaginator
    This paginator provides a way to iterate through the logged-in user's subscribed subreddits
    Paginator<T extends Thing>
    Represents the basic concept of a paginator
    SpecificPaginator
    This class provides a way to iterate through a list of Submissions by their names.
    SubredditPaginator
    This class is used to paginate through the front page or a subreddit with different time periods or sortings.
    UserContributionPaginator
    This class is used to paginate through user posts or comments via /user/{username}/{where}.json
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    AllSubredditsPaginator.Where  
    MySubredditsPaginator.Where  
    Sorting
    Represents how the Reddit API chooses what it returns in a Paginator
    TimePeriod
    Represents a time boundary in which the Reddit API will return models
    UserContributionPaginator.Where
    Used by UserPaginatorSubmission to fill in the "where" in /user/{username}/{where}
